commit.message:
fix: use built-in functools.cached_property in py3.8+

Use built-in functools.cached_property decorator in Python 3.8+,
and fall back to the 'backports.cached_property' only in older Python
versions.  This saves people from having to package this backport
on distributions that no longer ship Python < 3.8.

commit.message:
feat: add overwrite/automatic/manual cache policies

I realized that the previous policies didn't offer a useful level of
control over when properties would be recalculated, so I created a new
set of policies modeled after `functools.cached_property()`.

BREAKING CHANGE: remove property/object/class cache policies.
